reek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margaret Stighull was born in 1374, in Devon, England, United Kingdom, her father, William Stighull, was 34 and her mother, Elizabeth de Malston, was 30. She married Walter Reynell VII before 1383, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1374–":"1374–Surnud","1370–Male":"1370–Surnud","1374–Female":"1374–Surnud","1355–1423":"1355–1423","1362–1430":"1362–1430","1395–1475":"1395–1475","1340–1397":"1340–1397","1344–1394":"1344–1394","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","1395":"1395","1362":"1362","1394":"1394","1370":"1370","1423":"1423","1400":"1400","1344":"1344","1355":"1355","1365":"1365","1475":"1475","1397":"1397","1430":"1430","before 1383":"enne 1383","about 1395":"umbes 1395",", Devon, , England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"1374–":"1374–Kuollut","1370–Male":"1370–Kuollut","1374–Female":"1374–Kuollut","1355–1423":"1355–1423","1362–1430":"1362–1430","1395–1475":"1395–1475","1340–1397":"1340–1397","1344–1394":"1344–1394","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","1395":"1395","1362":"1362","1394":"1394","1370":"1370","1423":"1423","1400":"1400","1344":"1344","1355":"1355","1365":"1365","1475":"1475","1397":"1397","1430":"1430","before 1383":"ennen vuotta 1383","about 1395":"noin 1395",", Devon, , England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"1374–":"1374–Décédée","1370–Male":"1370–Décédé","1374–Female":"1374–Décédée","1355–1423":"1355–1423","1362–1430":"1362–1430","1395–1475":"1395–1475","1340–1397":"1340–1397","1344–1394":"1344–1394","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","1395":"1395","1362":"1362","1394":"1394","1370":"1370","1423":"1423","1400":"1400","1344":"1344","1355":"1355","1365":"1365","1475":"1475","1397":"1397","1430":"1430","before 1383":"avant 1383","about 1395":"environ 1395",", Devon, , England":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre","Devon, Engla